2026-02-10 19:39:50,323 DEBUG openai._base_client: Request options: {'method': 'post', 'url': '/responses', 'files': None, 'idempotency_key': 'stainless-python-retry-e230481b-2e02-4f5e-80c0-b6ba7c5b2ee2', 'json_data': {'input': "Translate the following Divento temporary exhibition content.\n\nRules (follow exactly):\n- Return ONLY a JSON object matching the provided schema.\n- Do not add citations, links, or URLs.\n- Avoid em/en dash characters (— or –); rewrite with commas or parentheses.\n- Keep all HTML tags intact in 'long' and return valid HTML.\n- Do NOT add extra blank lines/newlines.\n- For 'short': maximum 164 characters in the target language, keep natural phrasing.\n- For 'name': translate only what should be translated; keep proper nouns/titles as appropriate.\n- For zh-CN: translate ALL prose into Simplified Chinese; Latin script is allowed ONLY for proper nouns and official artwork/series titles.\n\nEnglish inputs:\n- name_en: La grande aventure du savoir médical, Exhibition, Institut du monde arabe, Paris: 13 October 2026-10 January 2027\n- short_en: Follow Arab medical thinkers as they test cures, map anatomy and refine surgery, from Avicenna’s pages to apothecary jars and steel tools.\nlong_en_html:\n<p>Medical history feels worth the trip when it gets messy and real: how to stop bleeding, how to ease fever, how to organise care when a city is hit by illness. That’s what makes La grande aventure du savoir médical so engaging. It sticks to practical questions and shows the working methods behind them, from careful observation to disciplined note-taking and plenty of argument along the way.</p><p>At The Institut du monde arabe in Paris, the story leans hard on books as tools. A clear highlight is seeing major texts treated as living reference works rather than museum relics, with dense handwriting, diagrams, and marginal corrections. Ibn Sina (Avicenna) and the Canon of Medicine get pride of place as a system-builder’s manual; al-Razi’s al-Hawi comes through as a clinician’s notebook on symptoms and treatments; and al-Zahrawi’s al-Tasrif brings surgical know-how down to earth with drawings and step-by-step thinking.</p><p>Two don’t-miss elements keep everything tangible. First, the surgery material: metal instruments, illustrated techniques, and the stark logic of interventions like cauterisation, stitching, and setting fractures. It’s not romanticised, and that honesty gives the subject weight. Second, the pharmacy thread, where remedies read like recipes and the objects feel everyday: jars, bottles, balances, and lists of plants, resins, and minerals prepared with measured care. It underlines how much of medicine sits between the library and the workshop.</p><p>The hidden gem is the quieter evidence of medical life beyond big names: notes on hygiene and diet, advice on prevention, and documents that hint at how care was organised through institutions and charitable networks. It adds social texture to the manuscripts and tools, and it also explains how knowledge travelled, got translated, and survived contact with other traditions. There’s a steady sense of medicine as a shared craft, built by teachers, copyists, pharmacists, and patients as much as by celebrated scholars.</p>\n", 'max_output_tokens': 9000, 'model': 'gpt-5.2', 'reasoning': {'effort': 'medium'}, 'text': {'verbosity': 'low', 'format': {'type': 'json_schema', 'name': 'temp_translation_bundle', 'strict': True, 'schema': {'type': 'object', 'additionalProperties': False, 'properties': {'fr': {'type': 'object', 'additionalProperties': False, 'properties': {'name': {'type': 'string'}, 'short': {'type': 'string'}, 'long': {'type': 'string'}}, 'required': ['name', 'short', 'long']}, 'es': {'type': 'object', 'additionalProperties': False, 'properties': {'name': {'type': 'string'}, 'short': {'type': 'string'}, 'long': {'type': 'string'}}, 'required': ['name', 'short', 'long']}, 'it': {'type': 'object', 'additionalProperties': False, 'properties': {'name': {'type': 'string'}, 'short': {'type': 'string'}, 'long': {'type': 'string'}}, 'required': ['name', 'short', 'long']}, 'ru': {'type': 'object', 'additionalProperties': False, 'properties': {'name': {'type': 'string'}, 'short': {'type': 'string'}, 'long': {'type': 'string'}}, 'required': ['name', 'short', 'long']}, 'zh-CN': {'type': 'object', 'additionalProperties': False, 'properties': {'name': {'type': 'string'}, 'short': {'type': 'string'}, 'long': {'type': 'string'}}, 'required': ['name', 'short', 'long']}}, 'required': ['fr', 'es', 'it', 'ru', 'zh-CN']}}}}}
